This paper deals with rateless codes for communication over Gaussian channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of layered encoding and successive decoding, which are common techniques in network information theory (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of repetition and time-varying layer weights, which are relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of decoding algorithms, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
